Screen : Screen class.
Represent your Screen.

Member of SDLo namespace.

Constructor :
Screen::Screen()

Setters :
Screen::setWidth(int width)
Set the width of the screen
    param : 
        int width -> width

    return : nothing

Screen::setHight(int height)
Set the height of the screen
    param : 
        int height -> height

    return :
        void


Screen::setTitle(char const title[])
Set the title of the window
    param :
        char const title[] -> title of the window
    return : 
        void

Getters : 
Screen::getWidth()
return :
    width

Screen::getHeight()
return :  
    height

Screen::videoStarted()
return :
    true if video is started

Screen::isAlive()
return :    
    true if aplication have to continue
    false if aplication have to stop

Screen::getScreen()
return :
    A pointer to the Screen object itself

Other methods :
Screen::startVideo()
Start the SDL Video Subsystem with the parameters set on the object
return :
    void

Screen::updateVideo()
Refresh the window
return :
    void

Screen::testEvent()
Request testing of events
The kind of test is set by the "waitEvent" atribute. If waitEvent is true (false by default) wait for someting hapening on the window
return :
    void

Screen::addSprite(Sprite* sprite = new Sprite)
Add a sprite to the 2d world
If no sprite specified, it will create a new one.
return :
    pointer to the sprite added on the SDLo 2d world

